-- China shares end down despite afternoon bank rally
-- By Natalie Thomas
-- Thu Mar 27, 2014 03:16AM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, March 27 (Reuters) - China shares shed gains in late trading on a see-saw Thursday, ending down after though banking stocks rose for much of the afternoon on rumours the central bank may cut its reserve requirements.

The Shanghai Composite Index <.SSEC> ended down 0.8 percent at 2046.6 points. The CSI300 <.CSI300> of the leading Shanghai and Shenzhen A-share listings declined by 0.7 percent. The CSI300 banking sub-index <.CSI300BI> closed up 1 percent. Minsheng Bank <.600016.SS> rose 3.6 percent, and Shanghai Pudong Development Bank Co Ltd <.600000.SS> 1.2 percent. China Citic Bank Corp <601998.SS> shares closed up 1.97 percent on news that its parent CITIC Group would inject its main operating arm CITIC Pacific Ltd <0267.HK> [ID:nnL4N0MO0B].  Bank of China <601988.SS> gained 0.8 percent after posting an above-estimate 11 percent increase in fourth quarter profits. [ID:nL4N0MN26Y].